A POINT MAY BE CONSTRUCTED BY THE FOLLOWING OPTIONS:

1 : THE 3 COORDINATES X Y Z
    Example: POINT1; I; 1; 0.0001; 1E-2; 0; 

2 : THE CYLINDRICAL COORDINATES R TETA Z  WITH
    R    the RADIUS,
    TETA the LONGITUDE (angle (OX,OR)),
    Z    the COTE; 
    Example: POINT2; I; 2; 1; 90; 1;
              
3 : THE SPHERICAL COORDINATES R TETA PHI WITH
    R    the RADIUS,
    TETA the LONGITUDE (angle(OX,projection sur plan OXY de OR ),
    PHI  the LATITUDE  (angle(planXOY,OR) ; 
    Example: POINT3; I; 3; 1; 90.0; 45.0;

35: EXTRACTION OF VERTICES OF A LINE
    Give the number of the first and last vertex
    to extract of the line
    Example: POINT35; I; 35; LINE; 2; 25;

36: EXTRACTION OF VERTICES OF A PLSVO of which
    the 3 coordinates x,y,z give return true to the call of
    a logical User's function
    Example: POINT36; I; 36; LINE; CONTOUR; 
             deffunc PLANXY(x,y,z); PLANXY = (z=0); endfunc;
             PLANXY;
    extract the vertices on the XY plane of the line CONTOUR

50: MAPPING OF A POINT by a predefined mapping
    Example: POINT50; LINE_SYMETRY; 50; P1;
             The point POINT50 is the image of point P1
             by the mapping LINE_SYMETRY

51: THE POINT IS AN UNION OF SEVERAL POINTS WITH A SAME NAME
    Example: POINT51; I; 51; 5; P1; P2; P3; P4; P5;

81: RENAME THE NAME OF A POINT
    Example: NEW_NAME_POINT; I; 81; OLD_NAME_POINT
             Attention to the order NEW OLD of the point!

82: DELETE THE POINT of which the name has been input
    Example: P1; I; 82;   {delete the point P1}
